	<h2>Panhandle Cowboy</h2>
	<p>Panhandle Cowboy is the classic description of cowboy life by master storyteller John Erickson. His observations about the Crown Ranch in particular, and the cowboy lifestyle in general, are filled with humor and pathos as Erickson describes the ranch, individual cowboys, roundups, wild cattle, and horses.
		Panhandle Cowboy is a treasured addition to the literature, life and lore of the American cowboy.
